    {
        "content": "<p>This kind of situation, where a <code>simpa</code> doesn't work because I should disable some lemma in the simpa call, is really annoying to debug because <code>simpa?</code> fails instead of telling me what lemmas it tried to use.</p>",
        "id": 500430056,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1739892849
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The only general way to debug this is to do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊢</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which is a painful code transformation to perform</p>",
        "id": 500430295,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1739892911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could <code>simpa?</code> output information about which lemmas it used even when it is failing?</p>",
